A function is a collection of statements that perform a certain task.
=> we use function because it divides the work load and increase reusability.
=> Method: function inside a class

=> Declaration:
    + def keyword
    + function name:
        - in Scala, function name can have characters like +,~,&,-,++,\,/ etc
    + parameter list
    + return type:
        - the return types of the parameters is required while the return type of the function itself
        is optional
    + =:
        - if the user uses this, the function will return the desired value.
        - if not, it will not return any value and will work as a subroutine
    + method body